---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  pageHeading="Coverage Map"
  description="Current and planned mesh coverage across Kansas City metro. Router 1 is live. Router 2 (west side) is the priority."
>
  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">
      Where the KC mesh reaches (and where it doesn't yet)
    </h2>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      Router 1 covers east side. Everything west of State Line is basically uncovered. This map shows what exists and what's planned.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Map Placeholder -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-blue/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue/5 to-kc-sky/10 p-8 sm:p-12 dark:border-kc-sky/20 dark:from-kc-blue/10">
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-kc-blue/20 text-kc-blue dark:bg-kc-sky/20 dark:text-kc-sky">
        <svg class="w-8 h-8" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 20l-5.447-2.724A1 1 0 013 16.382V5.618a1 1 0 011.447-.894L9 7m0 13l6-3m-6 3V7m6 10l4.553 2.276A1 1 0 0021 18.382V7.618a1 1 0 00-.553-.894L15 4m0 13V4m0 0L9 7" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h2 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Interactive map coming soon</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-base text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        Building the interactive coverage map to show live router locations, coverage zones, and planned deployments. For now, here's what you need to know:
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Current Coverage -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">What's operational right now</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-mesh-green/30 bg-mesh-green/5 p-6 dark:border-mesh-green/20 dark:bg-mesh-green/10">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-mesh-green">Router 1 — East Side (OPERATIONAL)</h3>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-mesh-green px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-ink-900">
            <span class="block w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-ink-900 animate-pulse"></span>
            LIVE
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Location:</strong> East KC (exact location not disclosed for security)</p>
          <p><strong>Elevation:</strong> ~15 feet above surrounding terrain</p>
          <p><strong>Estimated coverage:</strong> 5-8 mile radius</p>
          <p><strong>Areas reached:</strong> East KC, Raytown direction, portions of downtown visibility</p>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> Backbone router + MQTT gateway</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Planned Deployments -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Planned backbone deployments</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-red/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-red/5 to-sunset-amber/5 p-6 dark:border-sunset-amber/20 dark:from-kc-red/10">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">Router 2 — West Side (PRIORITY NEED)</h3>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-kc-red px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-cream-50 dark:bg-sunset-amber dark:text-ink-900">
            SEEKING HOST
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Target location:</strong> Johnson County or western KC (west of State Line Road)</p>
          <p><strong>Ideal areas:</strong> Overland Park, Shawnee, Lenexa, western KC proper</p>
          <p><strong>Estimated coverage:</strong> 5-8+ miles (dependent on elevation)</p>
          <p><strong>Impact:</strong> Closes critical gap, enables east-west metro backbone</p>
          <p><strong>Status:</strong> Actively seeking site host with elevation</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6">
          <a
            href="/guides/west-side"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-kc-red px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-cream-50 transition hover:bg-kc-blue dark:bg-sunset-amber dark:text-ink-900 dark:hover:bg-prairie-gold"
          >
            Help host Router 2 →
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Router 3 — North Metro (Planned)</h3>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-border-light bg-surface-200 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-ink-700 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800 dark:text-cream-100">
            FUTURE
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Target:</strong> North KC / Northland area (Gladstone, Liberty, Parkville direction)</p>
          <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> River crossing coverage, northland metro access</p>
          <p><strong>Priority:</strong> After Router 2 deployment</p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Router 4 — South Metro (Planned)</h3>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-border-light bg-surface-200 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-ink-700 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800 dark:text-cream-100">
            FUTURE
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <p><strong>Target:</strong> South KC metro (Grandview, Belton, Lee's Summit direction)</p>
          <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Complete cardinal coverage, southern metro access</p>
          <p><strong>Priority:</strong> After Routers 2 and 3</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Coverage Gap Explanation -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Why Router 2 is the critical piece</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>Router 1 (east) + Router 2 (west) = functional metro coverage.</strong> These two routers provide east-west backbone across the KC metro. Client nodes fill in density between them.
      </p>
      <p>
        Johnson County alone has 600,000+ residents. Currently, almost none of them can reach the mesh. Router 2 changes that.
      </p>
      <p>
        Routers 3 and 4 (north and south) complete the full cardinal coverage eventually. But Router 2 is what makes this network usable for the majority of KC metro population.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Client Nodes -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Client node density</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        The backbone routers provide long-range coverage. Client nodes (people like you running devices at home, in vehicles, on hikes) fill in the density and extend the mesh in local neighborhoods.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>As more people deploy client nodes, the mesh gets more useful.</strong> Messages can hop between client nodes to reach destinations beyond direct router range.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">If you're in Router 1 coverage area</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Deploy a client node. Even an indoor node helps fill density. Test your attic, test a window location, see what works. Every node makes the mesh more resilient.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-200 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-800">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">If you're west side (no coverage yet)</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Help find a Router 2 host site. Once Router 2 is up, then deploy your client node. Or buy hardware now and test indoor coverage—you might be surprised what works.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a href="/get-started/join" class="text-base font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        Join the mesh with a client node →
      </a>
      <a href="/guides/solar-residential" class="text-base font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        Deploy a residential router →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Get Involved -->
  <section class="mt-12 text-center">
    <div class="inline-block rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue to-kc-red p-8 text-cream-50 shadow-card md:p-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Help expand coverage</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-base opacity-95">
        Deploy a client node in your coverage area. Or if you have elevation west of State Line, consider hosting Router 2.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="/guides/west-side"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cream-50 px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue transition hover:bg-surface-200"
        >
          Host Router 2
        </a>
        <a
          href="/get-started/join"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-cream-50 px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-cream-50 transition hover:bg-cream-50 hover:text-kc-blue"
        >
          Deploy a Node
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
